",\"desc\":\"Wethersfield Magistrate to the New Haven Colony General Court\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Fact\",\"d\":\"from 1666 to 1672\",\"pl\":\"Newark, New Jersey, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Robert Was a Principal in the Settlement, Founding and Early Governance of Newark, New Jersey.Robert led a group of Milford (Connecticut) settlers, who were dissatisfied with the 1665 union of the New Haven and Connecticut Colonies, to the New Jersey Colony to negotiate with the Dutch for a prospective new settlement site. In 1666 this group bought land - called Pesayak -  from the local Indians and renamed the area Newark in 1667.\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1672\",\"pl\":\"Milford, New Haven, Connecticut Colony, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Robert leaves Newark and returns to Milford\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Civic Duties\",\"d\":\"from 1678 to 1683\",\"pl\":\"Hartford, Hartford, Connecticut Colony, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Deputy Governor of Connecticut\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Fact\",\"d\":\"1685\",\"pl\":\"Milford, New Haven, Connecticut Colony, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Governor Treat Granted a Patent to Milford to Protect Its Land Titles. As Milford had not received a grant of its land from royal charter, but from purchase from Indians, the title to all lands in Milford was threatened by Govenor Edmund Andros of the Dominion of New England, founded in 1685. Governor Treat's Patent protected the Town lands, as well as all lands held by Town residents.\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Fact\",\"d\":\"from 1683 to 1698\",\"pl\":\"Hartford, Hartford, Connecticut Colony, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Governor of Connecticut Colony (after its union with the New Haven Colony and the Milford Plantations)\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Fact\",\"d\":\"1703\",\"pl\":\"New Haven, Connecticut Colony, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Col. Robert Treat Acquires Acreage Which Will Become New Milford. Robert and representatives of about 120 others from Milford get a patent for 84 square miles of land at Weantinogue in New Haven County. Together with the town of Bridgewater and parts of Brookfield, this area became the town of New Milford.\"},{\"t\":\"MILITARY_SERVICE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Held the rank of major\"},{\"t\":\"MILITARY_SERVICE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Captain King Philip's War  Colonial Governor of NJ & ConnecticutSome sources identify him, not as major, but as ensign\"}],\"mem\":79,\"src\":36,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"93J6-M64\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Other\",\"d\":\"about 1608\",\"pl\":\"Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kingdom\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":0,\"src\":3,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"93MB-Z8Z\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":4,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"93PX-44K\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":8,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"93RS-DTZ\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":1,\"src\":1,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"93WR-TBF\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Immigration\",\"d\":\"1635\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Eng to America\"},{\"t\":\"IMMIGRATION\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1635\",\"pl\":\"British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Weymouth, England, to Massachusetts Bay Colony\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"15 children. Please see published list in sketch before changing.\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"Crewkerne, Somerset, England, United Kingdom\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"Maine, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"Dover Point, Dover, Strafford, New Hampshire, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"Kittery, York, Maine, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":12,\"src\":51,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"94DH-VBC\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":2,\"src\":13,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"94MZ-YZF\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":13,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"94MZ-YZY\":{\"e