,\"mem\":0,\"src\":1,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L4ZD-4CS\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":5,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L4ZD-4CW\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Other\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":0,\"src\":1,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L51W-ZTP\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Arrival\",\"d\":\"1637\",\"pl\":\"Salem, Massachusetts Bay Colony, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1638\",\"pl\":\"Massachusetts Bay Colony, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":20,\"src\":23,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L523-63P\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":0,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L55P-HS3\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"NOBILITY_TITLE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1651\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Sheriff of Angsley\"}],\"mem\":0,\"src\":6,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L55X-ZLC\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":6,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5B4-5KS\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"MILITARY_SERVICE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"24 June 1782\",\"pl\":\"North Carolina, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1800\",\"pl\":\"Chatham, North Carolina, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":1,\"src\":7,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5BJ-33V\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":15,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5BJ-33W\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Baptism\",\"d\":\"9 March 1645\",\"pl\":\"Switzerland\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"Sissach, Basel-Landschaft, Switzerland\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":0,\"src\":17,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5BK-R9G\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":1,\"src\":11,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5BR-C5J\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Arrival\",\"d\":\"1679\",\"pl\":\"Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":0,\"src\":6,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5BT-PM8\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":1,\"src\":3,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5CB-67Z\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":3,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5DM-SWC\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"immigration\",\"d\":\"13 April 1721\",\"pl\":\"New Orleans, Orleans, Louisiana, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":0,\"src\":2,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5DP-4G3\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":1,\"src\":12,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5F9-8J8\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Margaret Upton Patent 700 acres N side Rappahannock\",\"d\":\"4 July 1653\",\"pl\":\"Lancaster, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\" for transportation of 13 persons\"}],\"mem\":7,\"src\":28,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5FD-5SF\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":3,\"src\":2,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5FR-RZM\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":0,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5GS-7LH\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":0,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5GZ-SFC\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"processioning of St. Peter’s Parish\",\"d\":\"1689\",\"pl\":\"County Limerick, Ireland\",\"desc\":\"The county clerk entered a list of landowners in the county, in the only surviving processioning record prior to the formation of St Paul’s parish in 1794. The majority of names on this list are spelled differently (more poorly) than for the same persons listed in the register.   Not only did the clerk use imaginative spellings, but his handwriting must have been difficult to read, for the Colonial Dames 1905 transcription of the same record renders scores of names differently than Chamberlayne’s transcription.  At any rate, no “Eastor” is mentioned anywhere in other records, thus this is surely Francis Hestor. Processioning was a mechanism designed to avoid boundary disputes caused by faulty surveys and the removal of landmarks.  A Virginia law passed in 1662 required each parish to organize groups of local landowners to “goe in procession”, or walk the property lines, to examine and renew the boundaries. The law in this timeframe required that this be done every four years between September and March.  [In those days the year ended on March 24 and the following year began on March 25, so the timeframe was intended to be the last half of every fourth year.]\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"arrived in Louisa County, Virginia (then New Kent County), from England\",\"d\":\"1704\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Quit Rent Rolls\",\"d\":\"1704\",\"pl\":\"New Kent, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Francis is shown with 300 acres\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"The vestry book of St. Paul’s Parish has been partly preserved and published, and contains several entries for Hesters, all concerning the processioning of land.\",\"d\":\"14 March 1709\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"The earliest recorded St. Paul’s processioning, carried out sometime in late 1708 or early 1709, and recorded on 14 March 1708/9, shows that the lands of Edward Bullock, Richard Bullock, Francis Hester, William Talley, and Mark Anthony were processioned as one of 39 precincts within the parish. The processioners’ return stated that “Fra: Hester being an Ancient man was not Able to Travel to see our Land processioned, but he saw his own, and so he was very well satisfied.”\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"St. Peter's Parish Episcopal Church may have been where George and Martha Washington were married, as well as the burial place of Francis Hester.\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":4,\"src\":6,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5JM-V8F\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":1,\"src\":7,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5K9-MVG\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":0,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5KM-C8K\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Other\",\"d\":\"14 March 1709\",\"pl\":\"Ireland\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Find A Grave\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Memorial #103360181\"}],\"mem\":2,\"src\":5,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5L2-Z8Z\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Described as a Candle maker\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"mem\":1,\"src\":2,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5LG-CGN\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":0,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5LR-C95\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":0,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5LR-CJ3\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":0,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5LR-HS9\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\":0,\"src\":0,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5LR-J3Z\":{\"ev\":[],\"mem\