80\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"No headstone.  Burial unknown.  Many inaccuracies in online information. Please be careful.  \",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Choose good primary sources.  \"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Only one son named Daniel.  Daniel was BURIED in January 1661/2, not BORN in 1661/2.  \",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Please consult the ORIGINAL record.  \"}],\"mem\":10,\"src\":42,\"sketch\":\"\"},\"L5XJ-6JS\":{\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OCCUPATION\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1659\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Town treasurer from 1659-1660\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Note\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Proof his wife was a daughter of Roger Williams is found in the following deed: Early Town Records of Providence Vol. XIV Deed Book 1, p.253  24 Jun 1670.  I John Sayles...have bargained & Sold unto Stephen Arnold of Pautuxett ..a full Thirteenth part of a little Island undivided called ye Vineyard. ...may Containe about a quarter of an acre for which I have received five shillings in Tobacco, which was the full Sum & price I sold it for.  I cannot make a firme deed of the forest land, at presant because I have None myself yet of My ffatherin-law Mr. Roger williams.  The forest land he gave me.\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Note\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"No proof of birth date or location - There is no document showing John's place or date of birth - he was age 48 at his death or born about 1633.  He cannot be the man who first appears in the Providence records in 1645 as he would have been a child, but whether or not that earlier John was his father is not documented, but the relationship is possible.  No other parent has been found for John\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Note\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"NOT a son of the Dutch John Sayles and wife Phillip Soales. That John and wife Phillip had ONLY TWO DAUGHTERS.  PLEASE READ all notes and discussions.\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"TEN C